3.终身工作 频繁换工作

Some people believe that staying in the same job for a long period of time  is the best way to build a successful career, while others think that frequently changing jobs brings more advantages.
Discuss both views and give your own opinion.

- lifelong employment
- job stability / job security
- career advancement
- skill diversification
- career stagnation
- dynamic job market
- long-term fulfillment



In this rapidly changing world, adaptability has become a crucial skill.
In today’s fast-changing world, lifelong learning is essential.
In an ever-changing world, individuals must constantly update their skills.


In this rapidly changing world, people make an effort in their way to suit this society.
In this rapidly changing world, people are making great efforts to adapt to society.

In an ever-changing world, individuals face increasing pressure to adapt to modern society.
Some believe that staying in the same job for a long period of time provides job security and stability. While others contend that frequently switch from job to job offers greater opportunities for career success.

